---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Container Desktop — Podman, Docker & Apple&trade; Container desktop UI for Windows, macOS, Linux"
description: "A familiar, open-source desktop interface for Podman, Docker and Apple&trade; Container — local, remote over SSH, and WSL, the same UI on Windows, macOS and Linux. Free, MIT licensed."
demoReplay: true
---
<div class="hero-glow"></div>
<section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
  <span class="badge"><span class="dot"></span> Free &amp; open source · MIT · Linux · macOS · Windows</span>
  <h1><span class="sd">The super duper</span><span class="grad">Container Desktop</span></h1>
  <p class="lead">A familiar desktop interface for the free, open container managers — <b>Podman</b>, <b>Docker</b>, and <b>Apple&trade; Container</b>.<br/> Local, remote over SSH, and WSL, the same UI, everywhere.</p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" id="heroDownload" href="#download">⬇ Download for your OS</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/manual/">Read the Manual</a>
  </div>
  <div class="pd-callout">Looking for the official one made by the Podman team? That's <a href="{{ site.podmanDesktop }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Podman Desktop</a> — also great.</div>
  <div class="shot replay-shot" data-demo-replay="/replays/podman.json" data-demo-poster="/videos/podman.png">
    <div class="demo-replay-shell" data-demo-replay-shell>
      <div class="demo-replay-player" data-demo-replay-player data-replay-poster="loading" aria-label="Container Desktop demo replay">
        <img class="demo-replay-poster" src="/videos/podman.png" alt="Container Desktop demo preview" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="demo-replay-controls" data-demo-replay-controls aria-label="Demo timeline"></div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="trust"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="t"><span class="ic"><i class="fab fa-linux"></i><i class="fab fa-apple"></i><i class="fab fa-windows"></i></span> &nbsp;Linux · macOS · Windows</div>
  <div class="t"><span class="ic">◆</span> <b>Podman</b> · <b>Docker</b> · <b>Apple&trade; Container</b></div>
  <div class="t"><span class="ic">◆</span> Local · SSH · WSL</div>
  <div class="t"><span class="ic">◆</span> <b>MIT</b> licensed</div>
  <div class="t"><span class="ic">◆</span> On the Microsoft Store</div>
</div></section>

<section class="features" id="features"><div class="wrap">
  {% for row in features.rows %}
  <div class="row{% if row.flip %} alt{% endif %}">
    <div class="copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">{{ row.eyebrow }}</span>
      <h3>{{ row.title | safe }}</h3>
      <p>{{ row.copy }}</p>
      {% if row.bullets %}<ul>{% for b in row.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>{% endif %}
      {% if row.chips %}<div class="engines">{% for c in row.chips %}<span class="chip">{{ c }}</span>{% endfor %}</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="shot"><img src="{{ row.img }}" alt="{{ row.alt }}" /></div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div></section>

<section class="grid-sec"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><h2>Everything you manage, at your fingertips</h2><p>The essentials only — so it feels right at home from the first launch.</p></div>
  <div class="cards">
    {% for c in features.grid %}
    <div class="card"><div class="thumb"><img src="{{ c.img }}" alt="{{ c.title }}" /></div><div class="cc"><div class="ico">{{ c.tag }}</div><h4>{{ c.title }}</h4><p>{{ c.copy }}</p></div></div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="manual" id="manual"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><h2>The Manual</h2><p>Your setup guides, modernized into a real handbook — every engine, every platform, with copy-paste commands. Nothing left behind.</p></div>
  <div class="manual-cards">
    <a class="mcard" href="/manual/#linux"><div class="k"><i class="fab fa-linux"></i></div><h4>Linux</h4>
      <ul><li>Quick guide</li><li>Podman acting as Docker</li><li>Docker Desktop alternative</li><li>Sharing connection</li></ul>
      <div class="arrow">Open Linux guide →</div></a>
    <a class="mcard" href="/manual/#macos"><div class="k"><i class="fab fa-apple"></i></div><h4>macOS</h4>
      <ul><li>colima quick start</li><li>Podman &amp; Docker via LIMA</li><li>Podman acting as Docker</li><li>Apple&trade; Container</li><li>Sharing connection</li></ul>
      <div class="arrow">Open macOS guide →</div></a>
    <a class="mcard" href="/manual/#windows"><div class="k"><i class="fab fa-windows"></i></div><h4>Windows</h4>
      <ul><li>WSL setup &amp; requirements</li><li>Quick guide</li><li>Podman acting as Docker</li><li>Custom install · Tips &amp; tricks</li></ul>
      <div class="arrow">Open Windows guide →</div></a>
  </div>
  <div class="manual-foot"><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/manual/">Browse the full Manual →</a></div>
</div></section>

<section class="dl" id="download"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><h2>Download {{ site.name }}</h2><p>Free and open source — native packages for every platform.</p></div>
  <div class="dl-cards">
    {% for d in downloads.os %}
    <div class="dlc" data-os="{{ d.id }}">
      <div class="os"><i class="fab {{ d.icon }}"></i></div>
      <h4>{{ d.id }}</h4>
      <div class="meta">{{ d.meta }}</div>
      <a class="btn btn-primary get" href="{{ d.file }}"><i class="fa-solid fa-download"></i><span class="get-label">{{ d.buttonLabel }}</span></a>
      <div class="fmt">{{ d.note | safe }}</div>
{% if d.menu and d.options %}
      <div class="dl-menu dl-package-menu">
        <button type="button" id="download-{{ d.slug }}" class="dl-menu-trigger" aria-haspopup="dialog" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="download-{{ d.slug }}-menu">
          <span class="dl-current">Choose package</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i>
        </button>
        <div id="download-{{ d.slug }}-menu" class="dl-menu-panel" aria-label="{{ d.id }} packages">
          <div class="dl-menu-head" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span>Intel</span><span>Arm</span></div>
{% for row in d.rows %}
          <div class="dl-package-row">
            <div class="dl-package-kind"><span class="dl-option-head"><span class="dl-option-title">{{ row.title }}</span><span class="dl-option-badge">{{ row.badge }}</span></span></div>
{% for option in row.options %}
            <a class="dl-menu-option" href="{{ option.file }}" data-primary="{% if option.id == d.options[0].id %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}" data-format="{{ option.format }}" data-arch="{{ option.arch }}" data-label="{{ option.buttonLabel }}" data-note="{{ option.note | escape }}" data-text="{{ option.label }}">
              <span class="dl-arch-meta">{{ option.archLabel }}</span>
            </a>
{% endfor %}
          </div>
{% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
{% elif d.links %}
      <div class="dl-links">{% for option in d.links %}<a href="{{ option.file }}">{{ option.label }}</a>{% if not loop.last %}<span>·</span>{% endif %}{% endfor %}</div>
{% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div></section>

<section class="pubs"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><h2>Recommended reading</h2><p>Go deeper with Podman — books worth your time.</p></div>
  <div class="books">
    {% for b in features.books %}
    <a class="book" href="{{ b.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img src="{{ b.img }}" alt="{{ b.title }}" /><span>{{ b.title }}</span></a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div></section>
